{
  "texts": [
    "Denote the conjugate of the perturbation function P ⋆ (ϵ) by P † (λ):= inf ϵ -λ ⊤ ϵ -P ⋆ (ϵ).",
    "By definition, we can check that P † (λ) = -D(λ) for λ ≥ 0, which is smooth with parameter L D from Lemma 1.",
    "Application of duality theory to the perturbation function P ⋆ (ϵ) shows that P ⋆ (ϵ) is strongly concave with parameter 1/L D over E; see Appendix B.6 for proof.",
    "By relating the perturbation function P ⋆ (ϵ) to the dual function D(λ), we bound the gap of the constraint function h(x, y) when evaluated at π ⋆ p (λ ⋆ p) and π ⋆ (λ ⋆ p), in Lemma 5; see Appendix B.7 for proof.",
    "Lemma 5 (Constraint gap)."
  ]
}